%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20happens%20to%20sharks%2C%20dolphins%2C%20alligators%2C%20and%20other%20marine%20life%20during%20a%20hurricane%3F%20Experts%20explain%20why%20the%20storm's%20aftermath%20is%20often%20more%20deadly%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20blacktip%20shark%20swims%20near%20a%20school%20of%20fish%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20near%20South%20Africa%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f230a11e6afd00196a5eb3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResearchers%20studied%20how%20blacktip%20sharks%20travel%20when%20tropical%20storms%20and%20hurricanes%20approach.%3Cp%3EReinhard%20Dirscherl%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHurricanes%20affect%20marine%20life%20differently%2C%20depending%20on%20whether%20they%20can%20move%20or%20are%20stationary.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMarine%20mammals%20and%20fish%20often%20head%20for%20deeper%20water%2C%20but%20seagrass%20and%20oysters%20have%20to%20stay%20put.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAfter%20a%20hurricane%2C%20increased%20levels%20of%20freshwater%2C%20bacteria%2C%20and%20debris%20can%20also%20harm%20marine%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20strong%20hurricanes%20hit%20land%2C%20the%20uprooted%20trees%2C%20destroyed%20homes%2C%20and%20other%20devastation%20are%20highly%20visible.%20What%20happens%20in%20the%20marine%20environments%20where%20they%20churn%20water%20and%20disrupt%20sediment%20isn't%20always%20as%20obvious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20vast%20array%20of%20marine%20life%20lives%20along%20the%20Florida%20peninsula%2C%20the%20US%20state%20where%20hurricanes%20make%20landfall%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aoml.noaa.gov%2Fhrd-faq%2F%23landfalls-by-state%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20often%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Florida%20Keys%20have%20coral%20reefs.%20Near%20the%20panhandle%2C%20there%20are%20temperate%20marshes%20and%20seagrass%20meadows.%20And%20the%20plants%20and%20animals%20in%20these%20various%20regions%20respond%20differently%20to%20hurricanes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20not%20all%20hurricanes%20have%20the%20same%20effects%2C%20said%20Melissa%20May%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20marine%20biology%20at%20Florida%20Gulf%20Coast%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20storm%20surge%20can%20act%20like%20an%20unusually%20high%20tide%20and%20leave%20some%20marine%20environments%20relatively%20undisturbed%20during%20the%20hurricane%20itself%2C%20she%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20storm's%20aftermath%20can%20have%20its%20own%20devastating%20effects%2C%20from%20changes%20in%20salinity%20to%20an%20influx%20of%20sediment%20and%20bacteria.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20happens%20to%20marine%20life%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0d%3C%2Fstrong%3Euring%20a%20hurricane%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20typical%20year%2C%20about%2010%20hurricanes%20will%20develop%20in%20the%20Atlantic%20basin%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean%2C%20Gulf%20of%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Caribbean%20Sea%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhc.noaa.gov%2Fclimo%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20force%20of%20a%20hurricane%20can%20create%2060-foot%20waves%20that%20churn%20together%20cold%20water%20from%20the%20depths%20with%20the%20warmer%20surface%20water.%20Its%20currents%20can%20stir%20up%20sediment%20as%20deep%20as%20300%20feet%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foceanservice.noaa.gov%2Ffacts%2Fhurricanes-sea-life.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20NOAA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20marine%20mammals%20and%20fish%20can%20move%20to%20deeper%2C%20calmer%20waters.%20Researchers%20followed%20the%20movements%20of%20blacktip%20sharks%20during%20a%202001%20tropical%20storm%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1046%2Fj.1095-8649.2003.00250.x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20left%20the%20area%20before%20it%20made%20landfall%20and%20returned%20after%20five%20to%2013%20days.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20hypothesized%20that%20lower%20barometric%20pressure%2C%20temperature%20changes%20in%20the%20water%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fisheries.noaa.gov%2Ffeature-story%2Fare-fish-impacted-hurricanes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimilar%20cues%3C%2Fa%3E%20alert%20fish%20that%20a%20storm%20is%20imminent.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D6262adeddd13a8b47bae6eb31f07ea29c43810ca3f5b8650fb80b7dfaf55e0b6%26postID%3D64f22b2afe7de7351163b241%26postSlug%3Dhurricane-effects-environment-marine-mammals-fish-plants-2023-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41598-018-37527-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2019%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20increased%20waves%20at%20the%20surface%20stirring%20water%20at%20the%20seafloor%20prompted%20gray%20triggerfish%20to%20move%20to%20deeper%20water%20before%20hurricanes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20dolphins%20and%20other%20marine%20mammals%20don't%20manage%20to%20escape%20the%20path%20of%20the%20hurricane%2C%20they%20can%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fisheries.noaa.gov%2Fmarine-life-distress%2Fdisplaced-dolphins-post-hurricane-response%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecome%20trapped%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20ponds%2C%20levees%2C%20and%20other%20freshwater%20habitats%20where%20they%20can't%20survive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222619%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Several%20people%20hold%20a%20dolphin%20stranded%20in%20a%20ditch%20after%20Hurricane%20Rita%20in%20Louisiana%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f22cb21e6afd00196a5880%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHurricane%20Rita%20stranded%20a%20dolphin%20in%20a%20ditch%20in%20Louisiana.%3Cp%3EReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHurricanes%20can%20be%20deadly%20for%20fish%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%201992's%20Hurricane%20Andrew%2C%20an%20estimated%209.4%20million%20saltwater%20fish%20died%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwater.usgs.gov%2Fnwsum%2FWSP2425%2Fandrew.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Geological%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20found.%20Sediment%20may%20have%20clogged%20their%20gills%20or%20the%20pressure%20changes%20may%20have%20formed%20deadly%20nitrogen%20gas%20bubbles%20in%20their%20blood.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20storm%20swirled%20sediment%20in%20freshwater%20environments%20and%20turned%20the%20water%20anoxic%2C%20meaning%20oxygen-deficient.%20An%20estimated%20187%20million%20fish%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weather.gov%2Flix%2Fandrewanniversary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edied%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%20Louisiana.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHurricanes%20also%20impact%20stationary%20or%20slow-moving%20marine%20life.%20After%20hurricanes%2C%20%26quot%3Bseagrass%20beds%20and%20oyster%20reefs%20have%20been%20buried%20by%20shifting%20sediment%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Valerie%20Paul%2C%20head%20scientist%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnaturalhistory.si.edu%2Fresearch%2Fsmithsonian-marine-station%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESmithsonian%20Marine%20Station%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20an%20email%20to%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20lots%20of%20storm%20surge%20and%20wave%20action%2C%20that%20can%20physically%20uproot%20the%20seagrass%2C%26quot%3B%20May%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHurricane%20Ian%20swept%20almost%20250%20baby%20sea%20turtles%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.floridatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fweather%2Fhurricanes%2F2022%2F10%2F06%2Fhurricane-ian-baby-sea-turtles-florida-shore-brevard-zoo%2F8176761001%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20shore%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20Brevard%20Zoo's%20Sea%20Turtle%20Healing%20Center%20housed%20them%20until%20they%20could%20be%20re-released.%C2%A0%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20corals%20rely%20on%20waves%20to%20break%20them%20up%20and%20distribute%20them%20to%20new%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean.%20Hurricanes%20can%20also%20bring%20in%20cooler%20water%20and%20help%20offset%20some%20of%20the%20effects%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-barrier-reef-death-coral-bleaching-climate-change-2018-5%5C%22%3Ecoral%20bleaching%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20when%20too-warm%20water%20causes%20corals%20to%20purge%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foceanservice.noaa.gov%2Feducation%2Ftutorial_corals%2Fcoral02_zooxanthellae.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esymbiotic%20algae%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20provide%20oxygen%20and%20waste%20removal.%20But%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2F60354-how-hurricanes-impact-underwater-marine-life.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverly%20strong%3C%2Fa%3E%20waves%20can%20break%20up%20and%20kill%20corals%2C%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20happens%20to%20the%20ocean%20after%20a%20hurricane%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20powerful%20storm%20subsides%2C%20litter%20and%20waste%20can%20remain%20in%20bodies%20of%20water%20for%20months%20or%20even%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20debris%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-hurricane-ian-climate-change-adaptation-flooding-sea-level-rise-2022-10%5C%22%3EHurricane%20Ian%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20our%20estuaries%2C%26quot%3B%20May%20said.%20Dozens%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnbc-2.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F03%2F08%2Fvehicles-still-waiting-to-be-towed-from-fort-myers-beach-after-hurricane-ian%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecars%20and%20boats%3C%2Fa%3E%20leaked%20gasoline%20and%20other%20chemicals%20into%20Estero%20Bay.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESewage%20can%20also%20make%20its%20way%20into%20waterways%2C%20bringing%20with%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdo-beards-carry-germs%5C%22%3Ebacteria%20like%20enterococcus%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20E.%20coli%2C%20May%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERain%20and%20flooding%20from%20hurricanes%20also%20bring%20an%20influx%20of%20freshwater%20to%20marine%20environments.%20%26quot%3BThis%20can%20be%20stressful%20to%20any%20organisms%20that%20don't%20handle%20large%20changes%20in%20salinity%2C%26quot%3B%20Paul%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarine%20life%20can%20often%20tolerate%20some%20changes%20in%20salt%20concentrations%20but%20not%20drastic%20or%20long-term%20alterations.%20For%20example%2C%20alligators%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhurricane-ian-knocks-out-entire-section-florida-sanibel-causeway-2022-9%5C%22%3ESanibel%20Island%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20Hurricane%20Ian%20hit%20hard%2C%20were%20affected%20by%20the%20saltier%20ocean%20water%20the%20storm%20brought%20on%20land.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20alligators%20can%20tolerate%20salt%20water%20for%20a%20time%2C%20they%20cannot%20live%20in%20it%20indefinitely%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsccf.org%2Fblog%2F2022%2F10%2F21%2Fhurricane-ians-impact-on-keystone-species%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESanibel-Captiva%20Conservation%20Foundation%3C%2Fa%3E's%20Chris%20Lechowicz.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20marine%20dolphins%20can%20only%20live%20in%20freshwater%20for%20a%20short%20time%20without%20suffering%20serious%20effects.%20Overexposure%20to%20freshwater%20after%20Hurricane%20Katrina%20may%20have%20caused%20a%20deadly%20skin%20disease%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fsmart-news%2Fclimate-change-fueling-fatal-disease-outbreak-dolphins-180976663%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebottlenose%20dolphins%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreshwater%20has%20other%20effects%2C%20too.%20%26quot%3BRivers%20tend%20to%20have%20a%20lot%20more%20sediment%20than%20ocean%20water%2C%20and%20they%20tend%20to%20have%20a%20lot%20higher%20concentrations%20of%20nutrients%20from%20coastal%20runoff%2C%26quot%3B%20May%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20hurricane%20pushes%20river%20water%20into%20the%20marine%20system%2C%20it%20creates%20favorable%20conditions%20for%20the%20formation%20of%20large%20algae%20blooms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20manatee%20eats%20seagrass%20at%20Ellie%20Schiller%20Homosassa%20Springs%20Wildlife%20State%20Park%2C%20in%20Homosassa%2C%20Florida%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f22f671b7ced0019c6f020%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20Hurricane%20Ian%2C%20manatees%20around%20Florida%20starved%20as%20it%20became%20difficult%20to%20find%20seagrass%2C%20their%20main%20food%20source.%3Cp%3EMarco%20Bello%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20these%20cascading%20effects%20from%20the%20hurricane%2C%26quot%3B%20May%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20algal%20blooms%20after%20Hurricane%20Ian%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thetimes.co.uk%2Farticle%2Fwhat-happened-to-floridas-manatees-after-hurricane-ian-jwrn9lscr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edidn't%20allow%3C%2Fa%3E%20sunlight%20to%20reach%20the%20seagrass%2C%20a%20primary%20food%20source%20for%20manatees.%20This%20pu