ndhaa-tells-ndtv-4357397%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%E2%80%99s%20Economy%2016.5%20Years%20Behind%20China%E2%80%99s%3A%20Bernstein%20Research%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%2F14124415%2F2020_5img13_May_2020_PTI13-05-2020_000137B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%20is%20a%20median%2016.5%20years%20behind%20China%20on%20broad%20business%20and%20economic%20parameters%2C%20according%20to%20latest%20research%20by%20brokerage%20firm%20Bernstein%2C%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Foverall-india-is-at-a-median-16-5-years-behind-china-economically-123090300495_1.html%5C%22%3Ereported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBernstein%20measured%20the%20India-China%20gap%20by%20looking%20at%20various%20yardsticks%20that%20included%20patents%2C%20foreign%20direct%20investment%20(FDI)%2C%20forex%20reserves%2C%20nominal%20gross%20domestic%20product%20(GDP)%20and%20exports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20patents%2C%20the%20report%20found%20India%20is%20behind%20China%20by%2021%20years.%20In%20terms%20of%20FDI%2C%20India%20is%2020%20years%20behind%20China%2C%2019%20years%20in%20forex%20reserves%2C%20and%2017%20years%20in%20exports.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20nominal%20GDP%20and%20per%20capita%20income%2C%20India%20is%2015%20years%20behind.%20In%20consumption%20expenditure%2C%20it%20is%2013%20years%20behind.%20On%20gross%20fixed%20capital%20formation%2C%20it%20is%2016%20years%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20it%20has%20much%20catching%20up%20to%20do%2C%20the%20newspaper%20cited%20the%20report%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBernstein%E2%80%99s%20analysis%20is%20based%20on%20data%20from%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%2C%20the%20China%E2%80%99s%20National%20Bureau%20of%20Statistics%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Statistics%20and%20Programme%20Implementation%2C%20the%20World%20Bank%20and%20the%20World%20Intellectual%20Property%20Organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Findia-china-imports-trade-deficit%5C%22%3ETech%2C%20Infra%2C%20Scale%3A%20The%20Challenges%20Hindering%20India%E2%80%99s%20Transition%20From%20the%20%E2%80%98Made%20in%20China%E2%80%99%20Tag%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20growth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20being%20ahead%20of%20India%20in%20these%20parameters%20is%20understandable%20given%20that%2C%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20was%20only%20the%2011th%20largest%20in%20the%20world%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20India%20became%20the%20fifth%20largest%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20of%20%243.53%20trillion%20pushed%20ahead%20of%20the%20UK%E2%80%99s%20%243.38%20trillion%2C%20to%20become%20the%20fifth%20largest%20economy.%20These%20calculations%20were%20based%20on%20the%20numbers%20estimated%20by%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fbusiness%2F2022%2Fmay%2F22%2Fusd-5-trillion-economy-the-curious-case-of-indias-rise-to-the-top-5-2456444.html%5C%22%3Ethe%20%3Cem%3ENew%20Indian%20Express%20%3C%2Fem%3Eanalysed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20nominal%20GDP%20numbers%2C%20saying%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20trouble%20with%20GDP%20numbers%20is%20that%20they%20undergo%20a%20series%20of%20revisions%20and%20the%20final%20data%20comes%20only%20with%20a%20lag%20of%20two%20to%20three%20years.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20first%20estimates%20of%20national%20output%20are%20ballpark%20figures%20and%20are%20subjected%20to%20revisions%2C%20both%20upwards%20and%20downwards.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20also%20important%20to%20note%20that%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enominal%20GDP%20of%20a%20country%20is%20expressed%20in%20terms%20of%20current%20year%20prices%20of%20goods%20and%20services%2C%20whereas%20real%20GDP%20is%20the%20inflation-adjusted%20GDP%20of%20a%20country.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20piece%20in%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Epublished%20in%20July%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-will-soon-become-third-largest-economy-does-it-matter-1238134.html%5C%22%3Eanalysed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20GDP%20growth%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CAll%20high-income%20countries%20get%20into%20low%20GDP%20growth%20orbit%20thanks%20to%20having%20attained%20economic%20prosperity%20and%20falling%20population%2C%20whereas%20developing%20countries%20record%20higher%20GDP%20growth.%20Unsurprisingly%2C%20India%2C%20a%20poor%20developing%20country%2C%20despite%20not%20so%20impressive%20growth%20of%20about%207%25%2C%20in%20current%20dollars%20during%202013-2022%2C%20moved%20past%20these%20four%20countries%20to%20become%20the%20fifth%20largest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20India%20is%20far%20behind%20in%20terms%20of%20per%20capita%20income%2C%20the%20newspaper%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20India%20reduce%20the%20gap%20with%20China%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20aims%20to%20hit%20%2410%20trillion%20by%202030%2C%20a%20target%20which%20experts%20say%20is%20very%20achievable.%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20said%20that%20India%20can%20leverage%20the%20slowing%20down%20of%20Chinese%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAnnual%20GDP%20growth%20was%20only%203%25%20in%202022%2C%20compared%20to%208.4%25%20in%202021%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Bank.%20India%20is%20growing%20faster%2C%20at%207%25%2C%20in%202022%20and%20the%20expectation%20is%20that%20it%20will%20continue%20to%20grow%20at%20that%20level%20or%20higher%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20business%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20geopolitical%20tensions%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20have%20provided%20India%20with%20some%20new%20leverage%20%E2%80%93%20many%20global%20companies%20manufacturing%20in%20China%20are%20hedging%20their%20bets%20and%20India%20has%20managed%20to%20persuade%20the%20likes%20of%20Apple%20to%20shift%20manufacturing%20capacity%20to%20the%20country%20and%20also%20export%20a%20large%20part%20of%20its%20production%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20India%20also%20has%20a%20growing%20young%20workforce%20with%20labour%20costs%20lower%20than%20China.%20But%20China%E2%80%99s%20productivity%20per%20labour%20is%20far%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20manufacturing%2C%20India%20is%20heavily%20dependent%20on%20China%20for%20its%20raw%20material%20needs.%20And%20%E2%80%9CChina%20has%20become%20the%20manufacturing%20hub%20of%20the%20world%20because%20it%20is%20able%20to%20produce%20things%20at%20scale.%20And%20having%20produced%20things%20at%20scale%20it%20is%20able%20to%20sell%20them%20for%20cheap.%20By%20selling%20them%20for%20cheap%2C%20it%20is%20able%20to%20dominate%2C%E2%80%9D%20Arun%20Kumar%2C%20retired%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20the%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftrade%2Findia-china-imports-trade-deficit%5C%22%3Ehad%20told%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20despite%20having%20a%20growing%20workforce%2C%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findias-workforce-not-rising-quality-of-jobs-very-low-cmies-mahesh-vyas%5C%22%3Edoesn%E2%80%99t%20have%3C%2Fa%3E%20enough%20quality%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20the%20population%20growth%20could%20become%20a%20liability%20for%20India%20if%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20create%20enough%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693812636000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F05%