20shake-up%20in%20Ukraine%20since%20the%20start%20of%20Russia's%20invasion%20in%20February%202022.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A183%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fukraines-defence-minister-to-be-replaced-as-zelenskyy-believes-new-approaches-are-needed-12954647%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fukraines-defence-minister-to-be-replaced-as-zelenskyy-believes-new-approaches-are-needed-12954647%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fukraines-defence-minister-to-be-replaced-as-zelenskyy-believes-new-approaches-are-needed-12954647%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22BRICS%20is%20Dynamic%2C%20the%20G20%20is%20Not%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F04012257%2F53135604437_b0001ecc47_o.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIndia%20may%20believe%20it%20is%20in%20strategic%20competition%20with%20China%20over%20leadership%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20but%20the%20recent%20BRICS%20meet%20made%20it%20clear%20who%20is%20calling%20the%20shots.%20Watching%20from%20afar%2C%20the%20US-led%20G-7%20nations%20could%20see%20that%20China%20was%20the%20key%20determinant%20of%20the%20summit%E2%80%99s%20accomplishments%20and%20that%20their%20own%20influence%20over%20the%20developing%20world%20had%20diminished%20substantially.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20unsaid%20gain%20made%20by%20China%20was%20the%20deft%20shifting%20of%20its%20global%20geopolitical%20game%20%E2%80%93%20based%20on%20%E2%80%98common%20prosperity%20and%20cooperative%20security%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20from%20east%20Asia%20to%20the%2054-nation%20African%20continent.%20The%20attendance%20of%20some%2035%20African%20nations%20at%20the%20Johannesburg%20summit%20as%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20invitees%2C%20followed%20by%2050%20African%20nations%20attending%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Feng.chinamil.com.cn%2FCHINA_209163%2FTopStories_209189%2F16248999.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethird%20China-Africa%20Peace%20and%20Security%20forum%20in%20Beijing%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20August%2029%20is%20testimony%20to%20the%20attraction%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Global%20Development%20Initiative%E2%80%99%20(GDI)%20and%20%E2%80%98Global%20Security%20Initiative%E2%80%99%20(GSI)%20hold%20for%20the%20Global%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20focus%20of%20the%20China-Africa%20Peace%20and%20Security%20forum%20was%20on%20peacekeeping%20(most%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%202700%2B%20peacekeepers%20are%20in%20Africa)%2C%20counterterrorism%2C%20cyber%20security%2C%20humanitarian%20aid%20and%20military%20education.%20Thus%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%2C%20say%2C%20the%20French%20forces%20fighting%20in%20the%20former%20colonies%20of%20Mali%20and%20Burkina%20Faso%2C%20the%20Chinese%20People%E2%80%99s%20Liberation%20Army%20(PLA)%20is%20providing%20training%2C%20self-defence%20weapons%2C%20and%20military%20education%20to%20accomplish%20security%20through%20development.%20With%20its%20focus%20on%20%E2%80%98cooperative%20security%E2%80%99%2C%20Beijing%20hopes%20to%20secure%20Chinese%20infrastructure%2C%20interests%20and%20citizens%20working%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20appeal%20of%20BRICS%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20headline%20from%20the%20summit%20was%20the%20arrival%20of%20BRICS%20Plus%2C%20with%20six%20new%20members%20from%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20Africa%20and%20South%20America%20%E2%80%93%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20the%20UAE%2C%20Iran%2C%20Egypt%2C%20Ethiopia%20and%20Argentina%20%E2%80%93%20joining%20from%20January%201%2C%202024.%20However%2C%20the%20bigger%20story%20is%20that%20despite%20political%20and%20ideological%20differences%2C%20many%20nations%20from%20the%20Global%20South%20are%20queuing%20up%20to%20join%20the%20organisation%20which%20is%20just%2015%20years%20old.%20They%20hope%2C%20and%20perhaps%20rightly%20so%2C%20that%20collective%20and%20interdependent%20prosperity%20will%20cap%20differences%2C%20such%20as%20the%20ones%20between%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20Iran%20or%20between%20Egypt%20and%20Ethiopia%20over%20Nile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20three%20reasons%20for%20BRICS%E2%80%99s%20growing%20appeal%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20nations%20of%20the%20Global%20South%20want%20prosperity%20by%20new%20economy%2C%20which%20is%20a%20mix%20of%20physical%20and%20digital%20economies%20by%20use%20of%20Artificial%20Intelligence%20and%20big%20data.%20Their%20assessment%20is%20that%20China%2C%20which%20is%20seen%20as%20the%20driver%20of%20BRICS%2C%20can%20give%20them%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20the%20weaponisation%20of%20the%20US%20dollar%20against%20Russia%20has%20made%20many%20nations%20realise%20the%20need%20to%20boost%20trade%20in%20local%20currencies%2C%20especially%20through%20institutions%20like%20the%20New%20Development%20Bank%20(NDB)%2C%20which%20is%20the%20BRICS%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20the%20selective%20approach%20of%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20towards%20war%20and%20occupation%20means%20global%20trust%20in%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20so-called%20%E2%80%98rules-based%20order%E2%80%99%20has%20diminished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EChina%E2%80%99s%20Africa%20strategy%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20rich%20in%20minerals%20and%20commodities%2C%20the%20African%20nations%20are%20the%20poorest%20in%20the%20world.%20They%20were%20exploited%20by%20the%20industrialised%20western%20nations%20who%20exported%20their%20mineral%20wealth%20for%20a%20pittance%20in%20return.%20Instead%20of%20helping%20them%20with%20sustainable%20economic%20development%20through%20infrastructure%20and%20capacity%20building%2C%20the%20West%2C%20especially%20the%20US%2C%20exploited%20them%20economically.%20They%20also%20assumed%20the%20moral%20high%20ground%2C%20by%20lecturing%20them%20on%20democracy%20and%20human%20rights%20when%20expedient%20while%20ignoring%20similar%20violations%20elsewhere.%20The%20West%20also%20erred%20in%20treating%20the%20entire%20continent%20(with%20some%20exceptions)%20as%20a%20monolithic%20entity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20two-decade-long%20association%20with%20the%20African%20continent%2C%20China%20changed%20the%20way%20of%20doing%20business.%20It%20understood%20that%20each%20of%20the%2054%20African%20nations%20were%20unique%20and%20needed%20to%20be%20addressed%20individually.%20At%20present%2C%2050%20African%20nations%20have%20joined%20or%20have%20an%20understanding%20with%20China%20on%20the%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%20(BRI).%20Through%20the%20latter%2C%20%3Cspan%3Eroads%2C%20railways%2C%20bridges%2C%20hospitals%2C%20schools%2C%20and%20airports%20etc.%2C%20have%20been%20constructed%20in%20Africa%2C%20which%20has%20boosted%20trade%2C%20increased%20job%20creation%2C%20improved%20transportation%2C%20education%20and%20health%20among%20African%20countries.%20China%20is%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20top%20trading%20partner%2C%20with%20an%20annual%20US%24300%20billion%20trade.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWorking%20under%20the%20GDI%2C%20China%20built%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investxiamen.org.cn%2Fdetail_en%2F4471.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENew%20Industrial%20Revolution%20Innovation%20Centre%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Xiamen%20to%20further%20cement%20the%20BRICS%20partnership%20with%20focus%20on%20African%20nations.%20In%202022%2C%20China%20hosted%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbricsbd4sd.en.cbas.ac.cn%2Fnews%2Fdetails_34_270.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eforum%20on%20the%20development%20of%20industrial%20internet%20and%20digital%20manufacturing%20with%20big%20data%20for%20sustainable%20development%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20concluded%20the%20digital%20economy%20partnership%20framework%2C%20issued%20the%20initiative%20for%20cooperation%20of%20digitisation%20and%20manufacturing%2C%20and%20agreed%20to%20establish%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.most.gov.cn%2Fpressroom%2F202206%2Ft20220622_181227.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enetwork%20of%20technology%20transfer%20centres%20and%20data%20centres%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20further%20South-South%20cooperation.%20The%20purpose%20of%20all%20this%20is%20to%20prepare%20African%20nations%20for%20the%20industrial%20internet%20and%20smart%20logistics%20as%20part%20of%20the%20fourth%20industrial%20revolution.%20Earlier%2C%20China%20attempted%20this%20piecemeal%20in%20ASEAN%20(starting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechnode.global%2F2023%2F07%2F26%2Falibaba-cloud-sees-increase-in-demand-from-various-industries-in-malaysia-market-says-vp-qa%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBesides%2520launching%2520the%2520innovation%2520center%2Caccelerate%2520the%2520growth%2520of%2520100%2C000%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAlibaba%20Cloud%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Malaysia%E2%80%99s%20first%20global%20public%20cloud%20platform%2C%20and%20setting%20up%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdig.watch%2Fupdates%2Fchinas-tencent-cloud-launches-first-data-centre-indonesia%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efirst%20data%20centre%20in%20Indonesia%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20but%20geopolitical%20divisions%20within%20the%2010%20members%20grouping%20did%20not%20produce%20optimal%20results.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20promise%20of%20a%20fourth%20industrial%20revolution%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMobile%20broadband%2C%20underpinned%20by%205G%20wireless%20communications%2C%20is%20the%20enabling%20technology%20for%20the%20fourth%20industrial%20revolution%20which%20comprises%20the%20fusion%20of%20physical%20and%20digital%20economies.%20It%20essentially%20has%20four%20components%20for%20speedy%2C%20efficient%2C%20and%20cost%20effective%20trade%20and%20commerce%3A%20(1)%20use%20of%20industrial%20robots%2C%20AI%2C%20big%20data%2C%20and%20the%20internet%20of%20things%20for%20smart%20manufacturing%3B%20(2)%20smart%20logistics%20with%20fully%20automated%20ports%20where%20automated%20cranes%20move%20containers%20from%20automated%20warehouses%20to%20autonomous%20(driverless)%20trucks%3B%20(3)%20smart%20solar%20panels%20(solar%20parks%20being%20considered%20for%20funding%20by%20the%20NDB)%20to%20reduce%20cost%20of%20green%20energy%20for%20heating%20and%20cooling%3B%20and%20(4)%20the%20digital%20yuan.%20With%20smart%20logistics%20and%20smart%20trade%20backed%20by%20blockchain%20technology%20(distributed%20digital%20ledger)%2C%20the%20digital%20yuan%20could%20emerge%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20decade%20as%20a%20leading%20unit%20of%20account%20in%20the%20Global%20South%20and%20perhaps%20even%20world%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20put%20this%20into%20perspective%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20Huawei%205G%20roll%20out%20both%20for%20industrial%20(industrial%20internet)%20and%20private%20(mobile%20internet)%20use%20is%20far%20ahead%20of%20the%20US%20and%20western%20nations.%20With%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tomshardware.com%2Fnews%2Fhuaweis-new-mystery-7nm-chip-from-chinese-fab-defies-us-sanctions%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20recent%20breakthrough%20in%20indigenous%207nm%20chip%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20scalable%20production%20will%20become%20possible%20for%20use%20in%20data%20centres%20which%20require%20large%20numbers%20of%20high-performance%20computing%2C%20storage%20and%20server%20chips.%20Moreover%2C%20China%20leads%20the%20world%20in%20use%20of%20industrial%20robots.%20And%20it%20was%20the%20first%20nation%20to%20introduce%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fasia%2Fchinas-digital-yuan-transactions-seeing-strong-momentum-says-cbank-gov-yi-2023-07-19%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ea%20Central%20Bank%20Digital%20Currency%20(CBDC).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20area%20where%20China%20says%20it%20can%20help%20the%20Global%20South%20is%20in%20internet%20security.%20It%20is%20evident%20that%20the%20global%20internet%E2%80%94matrix%20of%20telecommunications%2C%20fibre%20optic%20cables%2C%20subsea%20cables%2C%20and%20satellite%20network%E2%80%94will%20get%20fragmented%20into%20perhaps%20a%20US-led%2C%20China-led%2C%20and%20maybe%20a%20European%20Union-led%20internet.%20The%20reason%20for%20this%20is%20that%20each%20grouping%20will%20safeguard%20its%20data%20which%20runs%20through%20the%20internet%20from%20cyber%20and%20information%20operations.%20Data%20is%20the%20source%20of%20geopolitical%20power%20and%20competition%3B%20it%20is%20seen%20as%20central%20to%20economic%20and%20national%20security.%20Given%20this%2C%20China%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20US%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.china-briefing.com%2Fnews%2Fchina-cybersecurity-regulations-what-do-the-new-regulations-say%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehas%20rolled%20out%20comprehensive%20regulations%20on%20cyber%20security%2C%20data%20security%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20personal%20protection%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcarnegieendowment.org%2F2023%2F07%2F10%2Fchina-s-ai-regulations-and-how-they-get-made-pub-90117%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20even%20generative%20AI%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20short%2C%20there%20is%20a%20strong%20case%20to%20argue%20that%20the%20US%20could%20lose%20the%20fourth%20industrial%20revolution%20race%20to%20China%2C%20and%20the%20Global%20South%20nations%20who%20are%20lining%20up%20to%20join%20BRICS%20are%20aware%20of%20this.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELeveraging%20China%E2%80%99s%20financial%20clout%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20support%20the%20Global%20South%E2%80%99s%20new%20economy%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20BRICS%20bank%20or%20NDB%2C%20which%20is%20in%20its%20eight-year%20of%20existence%20has%20grown%20substantially.%20This%20is%20a%20consequence%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20which%2C%20to%20the%20US%E2%80%99%20and%20western%20nations%E2%80%99%20chagrin%2C%20has%20delivered%20unexpected%20results%20from%20sanctions%20on%20Russia.%20Today%2C%20Russia%20has%20emerged%20as%20one%20of%20the%20fastest%20growing%20economies%20of%20Europe%20(owing%20to%20energy%20sales%20to%20Asian%20nations)%2C%20while%20Germany%2C%20which%20is%20the%20largest%20economy%20of%20Europe%2C%20is%20in%20recession.%20Moreover%2C%20non-western%20nations%2C%20which%20have%20not%20supported%20the%20US%20view%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20war%2C%20have%20realised%20they%20need%20to%20find%20a%20way%20out%20of%20dollar%20dominance%20(and%20the%20US%E2%80%99s%20arbitrary%20confiscation%20of%20their%20dollar%20reserves).%20One%20option%20is%20to%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fspan%3Etrade%20in%20local%20currencies%20within%20the%20framework%20of%20BRICS%2C%20the%20Shanghai%20Cooperation%20Organisation%20(SCO)%2C%20and%20the%20Eurasian%20Economic%20Union%20(EEU).%20For%20example%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globaltimes.cn%2Fpage%2F202305%2F1291620.shtml%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENDB%20has%20already%20issued%20yuan-dominated%20bonds%20worth%208.5%20billion%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(worth%20US%241.2%20billion)%20and%20hope%20to%20issue%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fbrics-bank-aims-issue-first-indian-rupee-bond-by-october-2023-08-21%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erupee%20and%20rand%20denominated%20bonds%20by%20end%20of%202023%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20NDB%20officials%20were%20recently%20in%20Delhi%20and%20Mumbai%20(for%20discussion%20on%20policy%20and%20regulations)%20to%20hasten%20the%20issuance%20of%20rupee%20bonds.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20issues%20that%20require%20immediate%20attention%20are%20(a)%20the%20need%20to%20develop%20cyber%20secure%20and%20reliable%20industrial%20chains%20and%20strategy%20to%20link%20BRICS%2C%20SCO%2C%20and%20EEU%20nations%2C%20and%20(b)%20from%20India%E2%80%99s%20perspective%2C%20the%20time%20has%20come%20to%20decide%20which%20fragmented%20internet%20it%20chooses%20to%20be%20with.%20India%20has%20already%20rejected%20Huawei%205G%20on%20political%20grounds%3B%20no%20security%20issues%20were%20flagged%20by%20Indian%20cyber%20regulatory%20on%20technical%20examination.%20India%E2%80%99s%205G%20has%20100%20per%20cent%20electronics%20(hardware)%20imported%20from%20different%20countries%2C%20which%20may%20not%20be%20acceptable%20in%20the%20BRICS%20industrial%20chains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20terms%20of%20achievements%2C%20the%20NDB%20has%20cleared%2098%20green%20infrastructure%20projects%20worth%20USD%2035%20billion%2C%20of%20which%2035%20per%20cent%20are%20in%20local%20currency%2C%20mostly%20yuan.%20Focussed%20on%20climate%20friendly%20projects%2C%20the%20NDB%20is%20considering%20big%20projects%20which%20help%20numerous%20nations.%20Thus%2C%20instead%20of%20individual%20solar%20projects%2C%20it%20is%20considering%2C%20say%2C%20a%20large%20solar%20park%2C%20perhaps%20in%20the%20Sahara%20Desert%2C%20which%20can%20benefit%20the%20entire%20African%20continent.%20And%2C%20importantly%2C%20the%20NDB%20works%20in%20close%20collaboration%20with%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3EAsian%20Infrastructure%20and%20Investment%20Bank%20(AIIB)%2C%20established%20in%202016%20with%20headquarters%20in%20Beijing.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Freview-of-international-studies%2Farticle%2Fperpetual-decline-or-persistent-dominance-uncovering-angloamericas-true-structural-power-in-global-finance%2F75536FC7435F72FC9AB4968D0509F019%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20former%20US%20treasury%20secretary%20Larry%20Summers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20AIIB%E2%80%99s%20establishment%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20remembered%20as%20the%20moment%20the%20US%20lost%20its%20role%20as%20the%20underwriter%20of%20the%20global%20economic%20system%E2%80%9D.%20The%20AIIB%E2%80%99s%20governing%20principle%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20largest%20contributor%20to%20the%20multilateral%20organisation%20gets%20the%20largest%20say%20in%20running%20it%20%E2%80%93%20would%20ensure%20that%20China%2C%20which%20has%20initially%20committed%20US%24%2050%20billion%20of%20the%20total%20corpus%20of%20US%24%20100%20billion%2C%20would%20rule%20the%20roost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EUS%20strategy%20in%20Pacific%20and%20Indian%20Ocean%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20this%20is%20happening%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20the%20decline%20of%20American%20power.%20The%20reality%20check%20on%20this%20is%20provided%20by%20the%20schizophrenic%20foreign%20policy%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration.%20It%20wants%20its%20annual%20US%24%20700%20billion%20trade%20with%20China%20to%20continue%2C%20but%20it%20is%20not%20willing%20to%20lift%20technology%20sanctions%20on%20China%20%E2%80%93%20on%20the%20pretext%20of%20safeguarding%20its%20security%20%E2%80%93%20which%20would%20help%20it%20leapfrog%20into%20the%20fourth%20industrial%20revolution.%20Since%20the%20third%20industrial%20revolution%2C%20based%20on%20communications%20and%20computation%20was%20driven%20by%20the%20US%2C%20Washington%20cannot%20reconcile%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20China%20leading%20the%20next%20revolution%20based%20on%20AI%20and%20big%20data%2C%20which%2C%20though%20entirely%20different%2C%20builds%20on%20the%20third%20revolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBacked%20by%20its%20security%20establishment%20(including%20its%20massive%20defence%20industrial%20complex)%2C%20the%20US%2C%20unable%20to%20compete%20with%20China%E2%80%99s%20BRI%2C%20GDI%20and%20GSI%2C%20has%20decided%20to%20play%20to%20its%20strength%3A%20military%20power%20(deterrence).%20The%20US%E2%80%99s%20proxy%20war%20against%20Russia%2C%20fought%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20Ukrainian%20lives%2C%20cannot%20succeed%20since%20Russia%20is%20not%20any%20another%20nation.%20Russia%20remains%20a%20global%20major%20power%20(like%20the%20US%20and%20China)%20with%20landmass%20across%20eleven%20time%20zones%2C%20thousands%20of%20nuclear%20weapons%2C%20huge%20energy%20reserves%2C%20a%20vibrant%20defence%20industrial%20complex%2C%20and%20with%20determination%20(as%20seen%20in%20the%201942%20battle%20of%20Stalingrad%20which%20changed%20the%20course%20of%20World%20War%20II)%20to%20defend%20its%20sovereignty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20the%20US%20which%20has%20assessed%20China%20to%20be%20its%20primary%20pacing%20threat%2C%20is%20doing%20its%20best%20to%20provoke%20China%20into%20war%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20strengthening%20its%20deterrence%20against%20it%20in%20the%20west%20Pacific%20and%20Indian%20Ocean%20Region.%20The%20Biden%20administration%20has%20created%20and%20strengthened%20numerous%20military%20blocs%20like%20the%20Quadrilateral%20Security%20Dialogue%20(QUAD)%2C%20AUKUS%20(Australia%2C%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20US)%2C%20JAPHUS%20(Japan%2C%20Philippines%2C%20US)%2C%20the%20trilateral%20military%20bloc%20of%20US%2C%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%20and%20so%20on.%20As%20part%20of%20its%20pivot%20to%20Asia%2C%20which%20continues%20from%20the%20Obama%20administration%2C%20the%20US%20military%20has%20increased%20its%20strength%20in%20Japan%2C%20South%20Korea%2C%20Guam%2C%20and%20Philippines%20in%20both%20newly%20acquired%20bases%20and%20by%20rationalising%20existing%20ones.%20At%20present%2C%20of%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.democracynow.org%2F2023%2F2%2F14%2Fdavid_vine_us_bases_china_philippines%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E760%20military%20bases%20across%20the%20globe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%202%2C50%2C000%20troops%2C%20313%20bases%20surround%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnable%20to%20snap%20the%20strategic%20partnership%20between%20China%20and%20Russia%2C%20the%20US%20has%20globalised%20NATO.%20The%20latter%20has%20forged%20military%20ties%20with%20Australia%2C%20Japan%2C%20New%20Zealand%2C%20and%20South%20Korea%20for%20interoperability%20between%20them.%20Worse%2C%20the%20Biden%20administration%20is%20equivocal%20on%20its%20stated%20%E2%80%98one%20China%20policy.%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.usni.org%2F2021%2F06%2F23%2Fmilley-china-wants-capability-to-take-taiwan-by-2027-sees-no-near-term-intent-to-invade%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20US%20joint%20chiefs%20of%20staff%2C%20Gen.%20Mark%20Milley%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20China%20is%20developing%20capabilities%20to%20unify%20Taiwan%20with%20China%20by%202027.%20This%20is%20a%20speculative%20statement.%20What%20if%202027%20is%20the%20timeline%20that%20the%20US%20is%20considering%20for%20starting%20a%20war%20with%20China%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EBRICS%20backstory%20is%20not%20Goldman%20Sachs%20acronym%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20back%20to%20BRICS%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20know%20its%20history%2C%20which%20is%20not%20what%20is%20popularly%20believed.%20According%20to%20the%20popular%20narrative%2C%20the%20acronym%20BRIC%20(Brazil%2C%20Russia%2C%20India%2C%20China)%20was%20first%20suggested%20by%20Goldman%20Sach%20economist%20Jim%20O%E2%80%99Neil%20in%202001.%20Inspired%20by%20this%2C%20the%20foreign%20ministers%20of%20the%20four%20nations%20met%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20(UNGA)%20in%202006.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDigging%20deep%2C%20it%20would%20be%20fair%20to%20say%20that%20BRICS%E2%80%99s%20roots%20go%20back%20to%20the%20Russia-India-China%20strategic%20triangle%20first%20suggested%20by%20Russian%20Prime%20Minister%20Yevgeny%20Primakov%20in%202001.%20Primakov%2C%20a%20long-term%20foreign%20minister%2C%20was%20of%20the%20view%20that%20this%20strategic%20triangle%20would%20best%20serve%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20east%20vector%20interests.%20His%20suggestion%20was%20rejected%20by%20both%20India%20and%20China%20at%20the%20time%20as%20they%20assessed%20it%20as%20an%20anti-west%20tool%20to%20counter-balance%20the%20US.%20Russia%20once%20again%20presented%20the%20RIC%20format%20not%20as%20a%20strategic%20triangle%2C%20but%20as%20a%20trilateral%20dialogue%20mechanism%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20UNGA%20in%202003%2C%20when%20it%20found%20favour%20with%20both%20India%20and%20China.%20Thus%2C%20it%20will%20be%20fair%20to%20say%20that%20the%20RIC%20trilateral%20dialogue%20mechanism%20helped%20the%20creation%20of%20BRICS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20this%20means%20is%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20peace%20and%20prosperity%20is%20linked%20to%20Asia%2C%20where%20BRICS%20as%20the%20progeny%20of%20the%20RIC%2C%20should%20not%20be%20abandoned%20in%20favour%20of%20G-20.%20BRICS%20is%20dynamic%20and%20evolving%2C%20whereas%20the%20G-20%2C%20which%20grew%20out%20of%20the%20G-7%2C%20will%20lose%20its%20sheen%20without%20the%20participation%20of%20China%20and%20Russia.%20If%20India%20chooses%20to%20be%20on%20the%20wrong%20side%20of%20history%2C%20it%20will%20end%20up%20as%20an%20observer%20and%20not%20as%20one%20of%20the%20drivers%20of%20%E2%80%98once%20in%20a%20lifetime%E2%80%99%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPravin%20Sawhney%20is%20the%20author%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20Last%20War%3A%20How%20AI%20Will%20Shape%20India%E2%80%99s%20Final%20Showdown%20With%20China%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693791856000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F04012257%2F53135604437_b0001ecc47_o.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fbrics-is-dynamic-the-g20-is-not%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20India%20chooses%20to%20be%20on%20the%20wrong%20side%20of%20history%2C%20it%20will%20end%20up%20as%20an%20observer%20and%20not%20as%20one%20of%20the%20drivers%20of%C2%A0%20%E2%80%98once%20in%20a%20lifetime%E2%80%99%20change.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fbrics-is-dynamic-the-g20-is-not%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20American%20US%20presidential%20candidate%20Ramaswamy%20calls%20for%20'strategic%20clarity'%20on%20Taiwan%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693791587000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103336247%2Cimgsize-26314.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Findian-american-us-presidential-candidate-ramaswamy-calls-for-strategic-clarity-on-taiwan%2Farticleshow%2F103336229.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3